import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['x'], data['y'])
    plt.title('What is the correlation between x and y?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('x')
    plt.ylabel('y')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['x'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['x'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['x'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['x'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['x'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('x')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['y'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['y'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['y'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['y'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['y'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('y')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of y?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot([data['x'], data['y']])
    ax.set_xticklabels(['x', 'y'])
    ax.set_ylabel('Values')
    plt.title('What is the range of x and y values?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
    sns.kdeplot(data=data, x='x', y='y', cmap='Blues', shade=True, shade_lowest=False)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of points across the x and y coordinates?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
